reut2-016.sgm, GERMAN METALWORKERS' WAGE TALKS BEGIN WEDNESDAY, Negotiations scheduled between themetalworkers' IG Metall union and employers to resolve animpasse over a new contract will start on Wednesday, the unionsaid in a statement.    IG Metall is demanding a 35-hour week, with a parallelincrease in wages of five pct. Employers Gesamtmetall haveoffered a half-hour shortening in the current working week, to38 hours, and an initial rise of 2.8 pct.    IG Metall, under newly-elected leader Franz Steinkuehler,proposed the talks on Thursday, after regional negotiations inthe northern part of the state of Baden-Wuerttemberg collapsed. REUTER&#3;
