reut2-016.sgm, CHINA FACES EXTENDED SORGHUM SHORTAGE, China will be short of sorghum in 1987for the sixth successive year because high production costs andlow profits discourage farmers from growing it, the China DailyBusiness Weekly said.    It said sorghum output in calendar 1986 was 5.34 mlntonnes, down five pct from the 1985 level, and prices on thefree market rose in January to 0.42 yuan per kg, up 14 pct onJanuary 1986.    It said sorghum acreage in 1987 is six pct lower than in1986. Sorghum accounts for 40 pct of the raw materials neededby China's breweries, it added but gave no more details. REUTER&#3;
