reut2-016.sgm, JAPAN SEES HIGHER MONEY SUPPLY GROWTH THIS QUARTER, The Bank of Japan said it forecastJapan's broadly-defined M-2 money supply average pluscertificates of deposit (CDs) will rise by about nine pct inthe current April-June quarter against 8.5 pct a year earlier.    Unadjusted M-2 plus CDs rose a preliminary 8.8 pct inJanuary/March 1987 compared with a nine pct rise a yearearlier, it said.    The bank said the forecast rise is due to an increase infloating deposits due to recent low interest rates and a shiftto private banks from the Bank of Japan of 400-1,000 billionyen by the recently privatised Japanese Railways. REUTER &#3;
