reut2-016.sgm, JAPAN CAREFULLY WATCHING MARKETS, SUMITA SAYS, The Bank of Japan is carefully watchingthe recent rapid rise of the Tokyo stock and yen bond marketsfor their impact on inflation, governor Satoshi Sumita said.    In a statement to the bank's regional branch managers,Sumita said the central bank was particularly monitoring themarkets because of the recent rapid growth of money supply. Hesaid he is also carefully watching real estate prices.    Sumita said he expects money supply growth to remain highfrom April through June. In March, money supply, as measured byM-2 plus certificates of deposit, rose at a year-on-year rateof nine pct. REUTER&#3;
